@dev Sets the contract active and allows for further interaction. Will lock all DAI in DSR.
      The deposit is equal to the DAI balance when this function is called and can never be changed.

@dev Submit a Transaction to return the deposit to the tenant. Requires two confirmations
 @return txnId The unique identifier of the transaction

 @param txnId The unique identifier of the transaction

 @param txnId The unique identifier of the transaction
@dev Withdraw all interest, leaving the remaining deposit and fees locked on the contract

@dev Withdraw an amount up to the trusteeFee to the account of the trustee
      This can only withdraw contract balance and accrued interest above the initial deposit value

devdoc.author: Matthias Nadler, University of Basel

params.txnId: The unique identifier of the transaction

constructor.details: Initializes the contract with the addresses. These values can never be changed.

params.landlord: Can receive payments for damages up to the original deposit amount
params.tenant: The owner of the deposit that earns the interest
params.trustee: Earns a fee for enforcing off-chain contracts via multisig

executeTransaction(uint256).details: Execute a transaction that has two or more confirmations

params.txnId: The unique identifier of the transaction

getConfirmationStatus(uint256).details: Calculates the confirmed status for every participant of a transaction.

params.txnId: The unique identifier of the transaction.

returns.confirmationStatus: as a boolean array like [true, false, true]         where the order is [tenant, landlord, trustee]

getTransactionIds(bool,bool).details: Get a list of all transaction IDs that match the filter arguments

params.pending: will include completed transactions if set to true

returns.txnIds: an array with all the transaction IDs that match the arguments

isConfirmed(uint256).details: Check if a transaction has enough confirmations and is ready to be executed      All transactions require two or more confirmations to be confirmed      The migrate transaction needs to be confirmed by the trustee

params.txnId: The unique identifier of the transaction returns true if the transaction is confirmed, false otherwise
The unique identifier of the transaction

start().details: Sets the contract active and allows for further interaction. Will lock all DAI in DSR.      The deposit is equal to the DAI balance when this function is called and can never be changed.

submitTransactionMigrate(address).details: Submit a Transaction to Migrate the funds to a new address. Requires two confirmations

params.dest: The destination address to send the DAI funds

returns.txnId: The unique identifier of the transaction

submitTransactionPayDamages(uint256).details: Submit a Transaction to pay damages to the landlord. Requires two confirmations

params.value: The amount of DAI (in wei denominations) to transfer to the landlord

returns.txnId: The unique identifier of the transaction

submitTransactionReturnDeposit().details: Submit a Transaction to return the deposit to the tenant. Requires two confirmations

returns.txnId: The unique identifier of the transaction

withdrawInterest().details: Withdraw all interest, leaving the remaining deposit and fees locked on the contract

withdrawTrusteeFee().details: Withdraw an amount up to the trusteeFee to the account of the trustee      This can only withdraw contract balance and accrued interest above the initial deposit value

devdoc.title: Rental Deposit Account with multisig and DSR locking

userdoc.notice: Lock a DAI deposit, gain interest and manage the deposit with help of a trustee
